<subSubSection id="32D4D6C27F68AA630BCBEA3DFEBF8F80" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="10" pageNumber="34" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7A7185497F68AA630BCBEA3DFEBF8F80" blockId="10.[151,1436,1729,2005]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1435,151,247]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="10" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F68AA620BCBEA3DFEA98856" box="[199,315,1801,1825]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="34" reason="1">
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F68AA620BCBEA3DFEA68856" bold="true" box="[199,308,1801,1825]" pageId="10" pageNumber="34">Remarks</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="BDCEFECA7F68AA620A4FEA3DFE7F8856" authorityName="Szelenyi" authorityYear="1981" box="[323,493,1801,1825]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Tricolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F68AA620A4FEA3DFE7F8856" box="[323,493,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="34">Tricolas fuscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described in the poorly known and now monospecific genus 
<taxonomicName id="BDCEFECA7F68AA620FD7EA3DFA0A8856" authority="Boucek" authorityName="Boucek" box="[1243,1432,1801,1826]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Tricolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F68AA620FD7EA3DFAA58856" box="[1243,1335,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="34">Tricolas</emphasis>
Bouček
</taxonomicName>
, but lacks most of the distinctive features of that genus, especially those of the propodeum (
<bibRefCitation id="1E5FF8B87F68AA620FCEEA19FF41881E" author="Boucek, Z. &amp; Rasplus, J. - Y." pageId="10" pageNumber="34" refId="ref7139" refString="Boucek, Z. &amp; Rasplus, J. - Y. (1991) Illustrated Key to West-Palearctic Pteromalidae. INRA, Paris, 140 pp. urn: isbn: 978 - 2 - 7380 - 0343 - 0" type="book" year="1991">Bouček &amp; Rasplus 1991</bibRefCitation>
). Instead, it belongs in 
<taxonomicName id="BDCEFECA7F68AA620AFFEA65FCA8881E" authority="Westwood. Its" authorityName="Westwood. Its" authorityYear="1833" box="[499,826,1873,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Mesopolobus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F68AA620AFFEA65FD1A881E" box="[499,648,1873,1897]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="34">Mesopolobus</emphasis>
Westwood. Its
</taxonomicName>
body shape, color, and slightly distinct mesoscutal setiferous punctures suggest it is a member of the 
<taxonomicName id="BDCEFECA7F68AA6209D1EA41FBA088FA" authority="(Walker)" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[733,1074,1909,1933]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Mesopolobus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dubius">
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F68AA6209D1EA41FC5488FA" box="[733,966,1909,1933]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="34">Mesopolobus dubius</emphasis>
(Walker)
</taxonomicName>
species group and therefore an association with cynipid galls is indicated. Within this group, 
<taxonomicName id="BDCEFECA7F68AA620886EAAEFC6E88C6" authorityName="Szelenyi" authorityYear="1981" box="[906,1020,1945,1969]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Tricolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F68AA620886EAAEFC3388C6" box="[906,929,1946,1969]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="34">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F68AA6208BAEAADFC6E88C6" box="[950,1020,1945,1969]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="34">fuscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
keys to 
<taxonomicName id="BDCEFECA7F68AA620F7CEAADFE8688A2" authority="(Thomson)" baseAuthorityName="Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1878" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Mesopolobus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocerus">
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F68AA620F7CEAADFA0E88C6" box="[1136,1436,1945,1969]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="34">Mesopolobus xanthocerus</emphasis>
(Thomson)
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="1E5FF8B87F68AA620A30EA89FE7888A2" author="Graham, M. W. R. de V." box="[316,490,1981,2005]" pageId="10" pageNumber="34" pagination="1 - 908" refId="ref8251" refString="Graham, M. W. R. de V. (1969) The Pteromalidae of North-Western Europe (Hymenoptera: Chalcidoidea). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Supplement 16, 1 - 908. http: // www. nhm. ac. uk / resources / research-curation / projects / chalcidoids / pdf _ X / Graham 969. pdf" type="journal article" year="1969">Graham (1969)</bibRefCitation>
because of its short mesosoma and yellowish antennae (
<figureCitation id="E2F599CC7F68AA620F74EA89FB6D88A2" box="[1144,1279,1981,2005]" captionStart="FIGURES 31–36" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1744,1767]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,303,1722]" captionTargetId="figure-99@11.[151,1436,303,1722]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 31–36. Mesopolobus fuscus ♀ holotype: 31, Body, lateral view; 32: Head and antennae, dorsal view; 33, Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 34, Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 35, Fore wing, dorsal view; 36, Metasoma, dorsal view." pageId="10" pageNumber="34">Figs 32, 36</figureCitation>
). I hesitate to synonymize 
<taxonomicName id="BDCEFECA7F69AA630A25EDADFE0A8FC7" authorityName="Szelenyi" authorityYear="1981" box="[297,408,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Tricolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscus">
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F69AA630A25EDADFED28FC7" box="[297,320,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="35">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F69AA630A5EEDACFE0A8FC7" box="[338,408,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="35">fuscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
under 
<taxonomicName id="BDCEFECA7F69AA630AE1EDADFD0D8FC7" baseAuthorityName="Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[493,671,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Mesopolobus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocerus">
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F69AA630AE1EDADFD968FC7" box="[493,516,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="35">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F69AA63091AEDACFD0D8FC7" box="[534,671,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="35">xanthocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as I have not seen the 
<typeStatus id="A5753BEB7F69AA6308B2EDA3FBB78FD8" box="[958,1061,151,175]" pageId="11" pageNumber="35">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="BDCEFECA7F69AA630F5DEDADFA918FC7" baseAuthorityName="Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[1105,1283,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Mesopolobus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocerus">
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F69AA630F5DEDADFBFA8FC7" box="[1105,1128,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="35">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F69AA630F76EDACFA918FC7" box="[1146,1283,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="35">xanthocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Attempts to contact the Lund University Zoological Museum in order to examine the 
<typeStatus id="A5753BEB7F69AA630F01ED88FBE18FA3" box="[1037,1139,188,212]" pageId="11" pageNumber="35">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="BDCEFECA7F69AA630FA8ED89FACA8FA3" baseAuthorityName="Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1878" box="[1188,1368,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Pteromalidae" genus="Mesopolobus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocerus">
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F69AA630FA8ED89FB298FA3" box="[1188,1211,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="35">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="48BA595B7F69AA630FC3ED88FACA8FA3" box="[1231,1368,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="35">xanthocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were unsuccessful.
</paragraph>
